Philippines Says Recycling Inflows Into Economy Is A ‘Challenge’

-- B y   J o e l   G u i n t o
-- 
2011-09-29T01:58:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/philippines-says-recycling-inflows-into-economy-is-a-challenge-.html
The  Philippines ’ “continuing
challenge” is to recycle capital inflows into the economy,
Transportation and Communications Secretary Mar Roxas said in a
speech in  Manila  today.  The Southeast Asian nation’s budget deficit this year may
be less than the program of as much as 300 billion pesos, said
Roxas, who is also a senior member of the government’s economic
team.  To contact the reporter on this story:
